The paper presents a method for extracting knowledge from a spiking neural classifier, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning for training the classifier, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on interpretability and feature extraction suggests that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's use of population encoding and time-varying synaptic weights suggests that it may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
